}

.centered-form {
    width: 60%;
    max-width: 812px;
    margin: 0 auto;
}","html":"<div class="rd3-page">
    <header class="header" style="background-image: url('/apps/molgenis-viz/img/home-header.jpg');">
        <div class="content">
            <h1>MOLGENIS-RD3</h1>
            <p>Data submission</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-filter" />
    </header>
    <div class="section bg-gray-050">
        <div class="section-content">
            <h2>Overview of the submission process</h2>
            <p>Before submitting data to RD3, register clinical and phenotypic metadata in PhenoStore. On a daily basis, RD3 will retrieve the latest data from PhenoStore including new submissions and updates to existing records.</p>
            <p>There are a few ways for submitting sample and experiment metadata to RD3. Please see our <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ms7ZtsbFwRjUknnuZ6S969rVi23_P4fO-t2h_Z4Sysc/edit?usp=sharing">data submission manual</a> for further instructions.</p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Enter data into one of the RD3 templates</strong></p>
                    <p>Download the relevant template(s) and enter information about the sample or experiments. There are required and optional fields.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Import data into RD3</strong></p>
                    <p>Go to the <a href="../updownload/">Upload page</a> and select the file you wish to import. Once the import process has begun, you will be shown the processing steps. If there are any errors, the import will stop and the error message will be displayed. Correct the error(s) and repeat the process until all errors are resolved.</p>
                    <div class="alert-info p-3">
                        <span><strong>Note:</strong> Data will not be imported into RD3 if there are errors.</span>
                    </div>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section bg-gray-000">
        <div class="section-content">
            <h2>Download submission templates</h2>
            <p>Templates are generated and controlled centrally. You can download them from the <a href="https://github.com/molgenis/projects-erdera/tree/main/templates">templates directory</a> on our GitHub repositry or by using the links below.</p>
            <h3>lrGS Templates</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <a href="https://github.com/molgenis/projects-erdera/raw/refs/heads/main/templates/Samples%20lrGS.xlsx">
                        Samples lrGS.xlsx
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="https://github.com/molgenis/projects-erdera/raw/refs/heads/main/templates/Experiments%20lrGS.xlsx">
                        Experiments lrGS.xlsx
                    </a>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <h3>OGM Templates</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <a href="https://github.com/molgenis/projects-erdera/raw/refs/heads/main/templates/Samples%20OGM.xlsx">
                        Samples OGM.xlsx
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="https://github.com/molgenis/projects-erdera/raw/refs/heads/main/templates/Experiments%20OGM.xlsx">
                        Experiments OGM.xlsx
                    </a>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <h3>RNA Templates</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <a href="https://github.com/molgenis/projects-erdera/raw/refs/heads/main/templates/Samples%20RNA.xlsx">
                        Samples RNA.xlsx
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="https://github.com/molgenis/projects-erdera/raw/refs/heads/main/templates/Experiments%20RNA.xlsx">
                        Experiments RNA.xlsx
                    </a>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>","javascript":"","dependencies":{"css":[],"javascript":[]}}
